Package edu.ncsu.csc216.issue_manager.model.issue

Class Issue

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.issue_manager.model.issue.Issue
  • public class Issue
extends java.lang.Object
    Concrete class representing the State Pattern context. An Issue keeps track of all issue information including the current state. The state is updated when a Command encapsulating a transition is given to the Issue. Issue encapsulates the state pattern interface, five concrete state classes and one enumeration.
    Author:
    symone

    • Constructor Detail

      • Issue

        public Issue​(int issueId,
             Issue.IssueType issueType,
             java.lang.String summary,
             java.lang.String note)
        Constructs a Issue from the provided IssueType, summary, and note. If any of the parameters are null or empty strings or the id is less than 1, then an IllegalArgumentException is thrown with the message “Issue cannot be created.”. The rest of the fields are initialized to the parameter values, null, false, or an empty object type as appropriate (Checked through the set methods). The note is added to a constructed ArrayList string object.
        Parameters:
        issueId - issue id
        summary - summary of the issue as a string
        note - string of note on the issue
        issueType - type of issue
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - is thrown with the message “Issue cannot be created." if there is an problem with any of the parameter.

      • Issue

        public Issue​(int id,
             java.lang.String state,
             java.lang.String issueType,
             java.lang.String summary,
             java.lang.String owner,
             boolean confirmed,
             java.lang.String resolution,
             java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> notes)
        The fields of the Issue are set to the values from the constructor, which are used from the IssueReader class. Throws and IllegalArgumentException with the message "Issue cannot be created." is there is a problem with any of the parameters (Checked thought the set methods)
        Parameters:
        id - issue's id
        state - the state of the issue
        issueType - the type of issue
        summary - the issue's summary
        owner - the issue's owner
        confirmed - the issue's confirmed
        resolution - the issue's resolution
        notes - the issue's note
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - is thrown with the message “Issue cannot be created." if there is a problem with any of the parameter.
